Forward by Larry Fink 
Carlos Agrazal has been improvising musically for decades. His swooping tone and wanton wails are part of the vocabulary. Jazz and the Latin beat are fixed within his soul. We all know that music is an abstraction, or is it? Looking at these images, we see that his eye is equal to his tone, but images are built from abstraction while addressing the passion of the real. Carlos hits the street with intense love and curiosity.    ... To read the full story go here: www.carlosagrazal.com/symbiosis
